description:
Tallest hotel in Paris, adjoining the Palais des Congrès

Bird's-eye view
At 34 floors, Hyatt Regency Paris Etoile is Paris's tallest hotel. You'll be off the beaten tourist trail in the 17th arrondissement, but right next to the Palais des Congrès. Here you'll find a shopping gallery and conference spaces, along with Porte Maillot Metro Station.

Bois de Boulogne
You'll find one of the biggest parks in Paris, Bois de Boulogne, a 20-minute walk away. Traveling with kids? Jardin d'Acclimatation, inside the park, has an amusement area and zoo. Business travelers appreciate the proximity of business districts La Défense and Neuilly-sur-Seine.

Vertical city
La Fayette restaurant offers a buffet lunch, à la carte dinner, and Sunday brunch. Make time for a drink and tapas at Bar La Fayette, where there's live piano most evenings. Or visit top-floor La Vue for cocktails and stunning views. The fitness center is up here, too.

Sleek, clean, modern
All 950 guestrooms in this super-size hotel are uncluttered and immaculately clean, with free WiFi, minibars, and 24-hour room service. For access to the Club Lounge, a free breakfast and a guaranteed good view, book an executive room on the upper floors. All rooms are non-smoking.

HOTEL_AMENITY.value:
In addition to the bar and restaurant areas, the Hyatt Regency Paris Etoile also has seating areas in the lobby. Also in the lobby is the business center, equipped with conference and meeting space, and a Baccarat shop selling fine crystal and glass. Wireless Internet access is complimentary in public areas.

A full range of services is on offer at the concierge desk. There is a separate ‘ice' room where food may be kept and a laundry room where they may do ironing. A fitness room is located on the 34th floor of the hotel, with views over Paris. A staff of firemen is in the building 24 hours a day, a legal requirement in French high-rise hotels; they also have medical training.

DINING.value:
Restaurant La Fayette - A large room off the main lobby area, decorated in deep red, offering á la carte and buffet French dishes throughout the day. Its terrace, in the main lobby area itself, is á la carte only.

Bar La Fayette - This bar also looks out onto the huge internal lobby area. A full range of alcoholic beverages is available. It is open from 11 AM until 1 AM.

Panoramic Bar - The hotel's bar on the top floor offers fantastic night-time views of Paris and a full range of cocktails and alcoholic beverages.

RECREATION.value:
Located on the 34th floor of the Hyatt Regency Paris Etoile, the fitness room offers unique relaxing moments. Equipped with the most modern facilities, guests can enjoy a fitness session with exceptional, panoramic views of Paris. Free access for hotel guests.

The recreational activities listed below are available either on site or near the hotel; fees may apply.

GOLD.value: Paris's tallest hotel offers you stunning views of the City of Lights. La Vue bar on the 34th floor is an impressive spot for a cocktail, especially at night with the illuminated Eiffel Tower in the distance. The rooms are sleek, the WiFi free, and you're right next to the Palais des Congrès with its shopping plaza and Porte Maillot Metro Station.

GUESTS_LOVE.value:
Guests Love
  • Stupendous views from all rooms of the 34-floor hotel

  • Elegant cocktails at La Vue bar

  • Convenient location for the Palais des Congrès and Porte Maillot Metro Station

  • Helpful concierge service

    • Keep in Mind
  • Classic rooms can be small and not all enjoy the best views

  • Since it's a large hotel, there can be long lines for check-out and elevators

END_OF_THE_DAY.value:
At the end of the day…
Our guests love the stupendous views at Hyatt Regency Paris Etoile, Paris's tallest hotel. Some guests bemoan the long lines at elevators and the reception desk, but most agree the view from 34th-floor La Vue cocktail bar makes up for that.
